## 5. Building It Step by Step

### Step 1 — Create the folder structure

In Obsidian, folders only appear once they contain a file. Create placeholder notes or use your OS file explorer / terminal to create the folders.

**Using terminal (bash/zsh on Mac/Linux, Git Bash on Windows):**
```bash
mkdir -p vault/01-Inbox/{Now,Fleeting,Someday-Maybe}
mkdir -p vault/02-Journal/{Daily,Weekly}
mkdir -p vault/03-Projects
mkdir -p vault/04-Areas
mkdir -p vault/05-Resources/{Literature-Notes,"Slip-Box/MOCs","Knowledge-Bank/Books","Knowledge-Bank/People","Knowledge-Bank/Quotes","Knowledge-Bank/Vocabulary","Knowledge-Bank/Raw"}
mkdir -p vault/06-Archive
mkdir -p vault/07-Templates
```
Replace `vault` with your actual vault path.

### Step 2 — Install and configure Templater (see Section 3)

### Step 3 — Copy the templates from Section 6 into `07-Templates/`

### Step 4 — Create your Dashboard (`00-Dashboard.md`)

